
@startuml

' Define classes and their relationships

class Location {
  +String name
  +String description
  +int capacity
}

class Exhibition {
  +String title
  +Date startDate
  +Date endDate
  +String theme
  +Employee coordinator
}

class Employee {
  +String name
  +String position
  +String department
  +Employee coach
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  +String itemTitle
  +String description
  +String historicalPeriod
}

class ArtPiece {
  +String title
  +Artist artist
  +Year createdYear
  +String medium
}

class Collector {
  +String name
  +String contactInfo
  +List<ArtPiece> pieces
}

class Artist {
  +String name
  +Country country
  +Date birthDate
  +Date deathDate
}

class Request {
  +ExhibitionItem item
  +Collector collector
  +ArtPiece piece
  +Status status
  +Date requestedDate
  +Date confirmedDate
}

class Coaching {
  +Employee junior
  +Employee senior
  +Date startCoaching
  +Date endCoaching
}

enum Status {
  PENDING
  CONFIRMED
  REJECTED
}

' Relationships

Employee "1" -- "0..*" Exhibition : coordinates
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Coaching : coachedJunior
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Coaching : coachSenior
Employee "0..*" -- "0..*" Employee : coachedBy (coaching relationship)

Location "1" -- "0..*" Exhibition : holds

Exhibition "1" -- "1..*" ExhibitionItem : includes

ExhibitionItem "1" -- "0..*" Request : hasRequests
Request "1" -- "1" ArtPiece : requests
Request "1" -- "1" Collector : from

Collector "1" -- "0..*" ArtPiece : owns
ArtPiece "1" -- "1" Artist : createdBy

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Location`**: Represents a space in the museum where exhibitions can be held.
- **`Exhibition`**: An event that takes place at a location, with a start and end date, and a coordinator.
- **`ExhibitionItem`**: A specific item or theme to be included in an exhibition.
- **`ArtPiece`**: The actual artwork being considered for inclusion in the exhibition.
- **`Collector`**: Individuals or institutions who own art pieces.
- **`Artist`**: The creator of the `ArtPiece`.
- **`Request`**: A formal request sent by the museum to a collector for a specific piece.
- **`Employee`**: Staff members involved in managing exhibitions.
- **`Coaching`**: Tracks mentorship between employees.

